Pride under Fire

Sociopolitical Documentary hosted by Ronan Starkey, published by SBS broadcasted as part of SBS Dateline series in 2016 - English narration 
http://docuwiki.net/images/9/9f/Pride-under-Fire-Cover.jpg

Information
------------------------------

49 members of the LGBTI community were murdered in the largest mass shooting in US history in Orlando Florida. In the wake of the massacre SBS Dateline has travelled to Louisville Kentucky to explore America's attitudes towards, guns, gays and Muslims, in a special report Pride Under Fire.
Dateline discovers that America has become a nation divided. With gay rights activists clashing with the gun lobby and anti-Muslim sentiment on the rise.
